# Arjun Biddanda, 2026.3.2

This folder contains all scripts used to run SINGER on real data. In the text below, we would show how these scripts are used by breaking down the steps.

This folder contains all steps used to estimate: 1) peaks of introgressed ancestry 2) deserts of archaic ancestry and 3) gene-set enrichments. 

All configuration details are in `config.yaml`. 

To run the pipeline (using data from Zenodo), include paths to relevant files in zenodo and run: 

```
snakemake -s enrichments.smk -j8 -p -n
```

(`-n` gives a dryrun, remove it to actuall run the full pipeline).
